  A space <fr:tex>X</fr:tex> is called <fr:em>Hausdorff</fr:em> if for any two distinct points <fr:tex>x_1,   x_2  \in  X</fr:tex>, there exist a <fr:em>disjoint</fr:em> pair of open neighbourhoods <fr:tex>U_1, U_2    \in   \mathcal {O}( X )</fr:tex>, of <fr:tex>x_1</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>x_2</fr:tex>.
